{{more sources|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox artwork | title = Martin Kukučín | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | image = Bratislava Medicka zahrada Martin Kukucin.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = The sculpture in [[Bratislava]] in 2008 | artist = [[Ivan Meštrović]] | catalogue = | year = <!-- If after 1583 CE, use {{start date|YYYY}} --> | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = Sculpture | material = Bronze | subject = [[Martin Kukučín]] | height_metric = <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = <!-- (i.e. in imperial units) --> | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = Corvallis: "Treatment needed" (1993) | city = [[Bratislava]], Slovakia; [[Corvallis, Oregon]], United States | museum = | accession = | coordinates = <!-- Only use for the coordinates (when known) of the artwork itself, i.e. not for the site, building, structure, etc where it is kept, otherwise leave blank (or omit): {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | owner = | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''''Martin Kukučín''''' is a sculpture of the [[Martin Kukučín|Slovak writer of the same name]] by [[Ivan Meštrović]]. Copies exist in [[Bratislava]], Slovakia and on the [[Oregon State University]] campus in [[Corvallis, Oregon]], in the United States. The statue depicts Kukučín seated with his legs crossed, wearing a suit and boots. He holds an open book in his hands, on his lap.<ref name=SI>{{Cite web|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!325721~!0#focus|title=Martin Kukucin, (sculpture).|accessdate=November 13, 2015|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]}}</ref>
== Bratislava, Slovakia == The statue in Bratislava is in the [[Parks and gardens in Bratislava | Medic Garden (''Medická záhrada'')]] in [[Old Town, Bratislava|Old Town]], near the Ondrejský Cemetery. ({{coord|48|08|58.1|N|17|07|09.3|E|type:landmark|display=inline}})
==Oregon State University== The bronze statue on the [[Oregon State University]] campus in [[Corvallis, Oregon]], dated 1977, is installed on the north side of [[The Valley Library]] ({{coord|44|33.905|N|123|16.598|W|type:landmark|display=inline}}). It measures {{Convert|6.5|ft|m}} x {{Convert|36|in|m}} x {{Convert|63|in|m}} and rests on a concrete base that is approximately {{Convert|13|in|m}} tall and has a {{Convert|9|ft|m|adj=on}} diameter.<ref name=SI/> The installation includes a plaque with the inscription, {{Small|MARTIN KUKUCIN 1860-1928 / AUTHOR AND PHYSICIAN / BY / IVAN MESTROVIC 1883-1962 / SCULPTOR}}. The work was surveyed and deemed "treatment needed" by [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]"program in April 1993.<ref name=SI/>
